    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="738"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d738">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 21, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 810.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                    758, of the 6th instant, inclosing copy of a dispatch from the British consul at
                    Erzeroum to the British ambassador at Constantinople, relating to the position
                    of American missionaries at Bitlis.</p>
                <pb facs="0733" n="1467" xml:id="pg_1467"/>
                <p>The considerate kindness of the British ambassador and of Mr. Oumberbatch in
                    furnishing information of this character is highly-appreciated.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
